<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">661.4116/76: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-08T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 8,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:17
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>1163. Kameneff<note n="14" xml:id="d886fn14">In the British House of
                                    Commons on Aug. 9 it was stated by the Government that “the
                                    Soviet delegation is composed of … Krassin … for trade
                                    negotiations; … Kamenoff … for political questions arising out
                                    of trade negotiations.”</note> arrived in England by destroyer
                                from Reval on Sunday last. Krassin has also reached London [after?]
                                short stay in Copenhagen.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>